## Limitations

This analysis is limited by the availability of sources and the inherent biases present in the selected materials. The ethical debate on capital punishment is complex and multifaceted, and this report may not capture all nuances or perspectives. Additionally, the lack of recent empirical data on the deterrent effects of capital punishment limits the ability to draw definitive conclusions. Further research, particularly empirical studies, would be beneficial in providing a more comprehensive understanding of the ethical implications of capital punishment.